AWARD-WINNING actor Vuyo Dabula has scored himself a major role. The actor, best known for his role as Gadaffi on the SABC1 soapie Generations: The Legacy, has joined 1Magic drama series, Entangled. According to the producers, the series follows Sharon, played by seasoned actress Phuti Khomo. She is an overachiever in her 30s, who is on the verge of marrying the love of her life, Sizwe (Vuyo Ngcukana). When her ex Julius (Vuyo) suddenly resurfaces after many years, everything Sharon and Sizwe have built is threatened. ALSO READ : DALOM KIDS: WE’LL ALWAYS BE AROUND! The producers added that the show was more than just about a love in danger. It will also explore the trials of life in the 30s, navigating friendships, masculinity, culture clashes, sexual orientation as well as what modern-day relationships look like through a humorous lens. The show has a star-studded cast, which includes radio and TV host Pearl Modiadie, who will lead the supporting cast as Andiswa. Other supporting cast members include Senzo Radebe as Reggie, Mpho Popps as Zweli, Didie Makobane as Zenani and Tessa Twala as Tshepi. Shirley Adonisi, the director of local entertainment channels at M-Net, told the People’s Paper in a statement that they were excited about the show. “Entangled is a ground-breaking and edgy show that we’re excited to share with our viewers. As 1Magic, we’re proud to contribute and create content that is interesting, lively, real and shifts mindsets. It’s part of our commitment to have local productions that our audiences can relate to,” she said. Tune into Entangled on 1Magic (DStv Channel 103) on Fridays at 9.30pm, starting on 7 January.